WEBVTT

00:36.161 --> 00:38.955
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

00:41.833 --> 00:43.418
-Oh, come on!
-What the hell?

00:51.134 --> 00:52.010
Oh dear.

00:52.093 --> 00:53.678
I'll take care of him.
No objections, right?

00:58.933 --> 01:00.477
Hold on!

01:01.853 --> 01:03.480
-Hold on.
-Excuse me, sir.

01:06.649 --> 01:08.485
Don't do this.

01:09.360 --> 01:10.445
Get off me!

01:12.489 --> 01:13.823
Oh no!

01:15.075 --> 01:16.034
Damn it.

01:18.286 --> 01:19.370
Don't go out.

01:20.747 --> 01:21.623
Hey.

01:23.750 --> 01:24.959
Sir!

01:25.043 --> 01:26.127
Please stop!

01:26.211 --> 01:27.128
That's enough!

01:27.212 --> 01:28.046
Come on!

01:28.129 --> 01:29.798
-Come on!
-I said enough!

01:29.881 --> 01:31.758
-Stop already!
-Jeez!

01:45.146 --> 01:46.731
-You didn't drink, right?
-Yeah.

01:46.815 --> 01:47.774
Where's your car?

01:47.857 --> 01:48.900
-Over there.
-Let's go.

01:48.983 --> 01:49.818
Okay.

02:12.632 --> 02:14.425
-Write your screenplays like that!
-"Write your screenplays like that."

02:14.509 --> 02:16.803
Every word was dripping with sincerity.

02:17.387 --> 02:20.265
It was the best thing
you've written so far.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.642
Write your screenplays like that!

02:22.725 --> 02:24.602
"Write your screenplays like that!"

02:36.573 --> 02:37.782
Welcome.

02:52.922 --> 02:54.507
Where is everyone?

02:54.591 --> 02:55.425
Oh, well…

02:56.551 --> 02:58.052
The police came, and…

02:58.136 --> 02:59.929
I'm not really sure.

03:03.308 --> 03:04.642
This is for the window.

03:04.726 --> 03:06.978
It's 200,000 won.
Let me know if it's not enough.

03:08.646 --> 03:09.814
Oh, okay.

03:09.898 --> 03:10.857
Did you…

03:13.109 --> 03:14.152
throw that rock?

03:15.945 --> 03:17.071
Yes.

03:18.072 --> 03:18.907
Why?

03:21.326 --> 03:22.410
Because I was bored.

03:23.036 --> 03:23.870
Bored?

03:29.459 --> 03:33.296
"37, Hyowon 2-gil…"

03:35.715 --> 03:36.591
Occupation?

03:51.981 --> 03:52.815
Occupation?

03:57.445 --> 03:58.488
He's a film director.

04:04.160 --> 04:04.994
Who are you?

04:05.995 --> 04:07.163
The producer in charge.

04:30.311 --> 04:31.229
Dong-man!

04:31.312 --> 04:32.522
-Dong-man!
-My goodness.

04:32.605 --> 04:34.148
Dong-man, are you okay?

04:35.608 --> 04:36.818
Hey.

04:36.901 --> 04:38.611
They won't take him for the same reason.

04:39.237 --> 04:41.990
They said his blood pressure and pulse
are normal, so he's not an emergency case.

04:42.073 --> 04:43.449
Did you tell them he got beaten badly?

04:43.533 --> 04:44.826
I did!

04:44.909 --> 04:47.328
I said he got the crap beaten out of him
and to look at his face!

04:47.412 --> 04:49.122
He says he's dying from a concussion,

04:49.205 --> 04:51.666
but when they ask for his name,
he says, "Hwang Dong-man."

04:51.749 --> 04:54.002
He answers every single question
the nurse asks him.

04:54.669 --> 04:57.922
He needs to act like he's unconscious,
but he can't even do that!

04:59.132 --> 05:00.800
How can I get my own name wrong?

05:00.883 --> 05:02.010
That's not what I said!

05:02.093 --> 05:03.469
Just don't answer!

05:03.553 --> 05:05.638
Keep quiet and pretend to be unconscious!

05:05.722 --> 05:06.597
Jeez.

05:07.223 --> 05:08.349
Whatever.

05:08.433 --> 05:10.518
If they turn him away again,
I'll just take him home.

05:17.817 --> 05:20.903
Damn it, why can't you
just pretend you passed out?

05:20.987 --> 05:23.990
That's the only way
to get admitted into the ER!

05:24.615 --> 05:25.700
That's embarrassing.

05:26.576 --> 05:28.578
How am I supposed to act?

05:29.704 --> 05:30.580
He's not hurt.

05:31.247 --> 05:32.290
He hasn't suffered enough.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.460
So, 120 over 80…

05:35.960 --> 05:38.004
What's your name, sir?

05:40.631 --> 05:41.758
Your name, sir.

05:42.842 --> 05:44.260
Your name.

05:50.975 --> 05:52.977
Here. How many do you see?

05:54.145 --> 05:55.021
How many?

05:56.689 --> 05:59.108
Why would you get that right, you idiot?

05:59.192 --> 06:00.735
How can I get "two" wrong?

06:00.818 --> 06:03.404
Just take him home, all right? Damn it.

06:03.488 --> 06:05.573
They said he's not an emergency case!

06:05.656 --> 06:07.158
Fine, let's just take him home!

06:08.284 --> 06:09.702
-What's wrong?
-Hey!

06:09.786 --> 06:11.704
-Hey!
-Stop him!

06:11.788 --> 06:12.997
-Hey!
-No, wait!

06:19.212 --> 06:20.463
He sure stuffed himself.

06:25.176 --> 06:26.385
Do you have any water?

06:26.469 --> 06:27.512
Right away, sir.

06:48.282 --> 06:49.158
It's snowing.

06:55.706 --> 06:56.833
Here.

07:00.837 --> 07:01.879
Take it.

07:01.963 --> 07:02.964
Oh, thanks.

07:17.019 --> 07:18.104
I feel better now.

07:38.666 --> 07:40.960
I'll give you 10,000 won. Let's just go!

07:43.504 --> 07:44.547
I'll give you 50,000 won.

07:46.966 --> 07:48.593
You've got to be kidding me.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.345
Hello?

07:51.888 --> 07:53.806
It's not a concussion.
There's no need to go to the hospital.

07:53.890 --> 07:55.099
Doesn't even look like he's in pain.

07:55.933 --> 07:58.352
He's going nuts
trying to fish out a 500-won coin.

07:59.187 --> 08:00.354
Yeah, 500 won!

08:01.314 --> 08:03.691
Out of the sewer! Where he just threw up!

08:05.401 --> 08:08.029
-Come on, hold it up right.
-It's not even 50,000 won.

08:08.112 --> 08:09.530
It's 500 won.

08:09.614 --> 08:10.948
-He was feeling nauseous, and…
-Lower, lower.

08:11.032 --> 08:12.700
-For goodness's sake.
-To your six o'clock.

08:12.783 --> 08:13.618
Good.

08:16.996 --> 08:17.914
What did he say?

09:13.719 --> 09:15.263
Park Gyeong-se, come out!

09:19.016 --> 09:20.184
I said come out!

09:22.103 --> 09:23.688
Damn it.

09:40.329 --> 09:43.040
I got cut off
because I was getting my ass kicked,

09:43.124 --> 09:44.417
but let me finish what I was saying.

09:45.751 --> 09:48.588
I had a lot prepared,
but none of it matters now.

09:49.880 --> 09:51.048
I'll just get to the point.

09:53.301 --> 09:54.135
The Eight Club?

09:55.720 --> 09:56.929
Forget it. I'm out.

09:58.139 --> 09:59.640
That's for you shiny people.

10:01.267 --> 10:03.728
I chose to live a worthless life…

10:05.980 --> 10:07.815
so what's The Eight Club to me?

10:09.066 --> 10:10.109
I'm sorry

10:10.735 --> 10:12.737
for sticking around when I wasn't wanted.

10:14.530 --> 10:16.407
You win at cutting down people with words.

10:17.533 --> 10:19.702
I'll give you that.

10:20.536 --> 10:21.704
But you know what?

10:22.580 --> 10:25.207
If I put my mind to it,
I can cut people down too.

10:25.958 --> 10:27.168
I just choose not to.

10:28.294 --> 10:29.170
Then do it.

10:30.421 --> 10:31.255
Go ahead!

10:33.174 --> 10:34.508
My jokes

10:35.217 --> 10:36.969
are just for blowing off steam,

10:37.928 --> 10:39.847
not cutting people down.

10:43.768 --> 10:44.769
Hey, let me ask you something.

10:46.604 --> 10:48.522
Why have you been so mean to me?

10:49.565 --> 10:51.275
You don't treat the others like that.

10:51.984 --> 10:54.737
But you always tear into my films
like a maniac.

10:55.738 --> 10:56.989
People ask, you know.

10:57.990 --> 11:00.534
"Why does Hwang Dong-man
hate Park Gyeong-se so much?"

11:02.703 --> 11:03.788
You must have a reason.

11:05.873 --> 11:07.500
A reason why you hate me so much.

11:07.583 --> 11:10.378
I only liked Hye-jin for a short time.

11:10.461 --> 11:11.462
Not that, damn it!

11:14.965 --> 11:17.218
There's got to be a reason
why you hate me!

11:22.348 --> 11:24.100
Because you hated me first.

11:28.687 --> 11:30.564
Why made you hate me so much?

11:58.634 --> 12:00.928
As of today, I'm leaving The Eight Club.

12:02.721 --> 12:05.224
I'm sorry I stuck around for so long
without taking a hint.

12:05.307 --> 12:06.517
THE EIGHT CLUB

12:06.600 --> 12:08.269
I'm leaving my crap behind.

12:09.103 --> 12:10.104
Just make a new group chat.

12:15.985 --> 12:17.153
THE EIGHT CLUB
LEAVE THIS CHAT?

12:21.449 --> 12:22.450
LEAVE

12:36.797 --> 12:37.882
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

12:39.300 --> 12:40.217
INVITE HWANG DONG-MAN TO THIS CHAT?

12:40.301 --> 12:41.135
CONFIRM

12:43.095 --> 12:46.223
The Eight Club
isn't something you can join

12:46.307 --> 12:47.975
and leave as you--

12:48.058 --> 12:49.101
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

12:49.185 --> 12:50.269
Goddamn it.

12:53.022 --> 12:54.106
Jeez.

12:54.190 --> 12:56.775
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

13:06.869 --> 13:09.079
They used to be inseparable.

13:10.122 --> 13:11.957
I don't know how they ended up like this.

13:12.041 --> 13:14.168
What? They used to be close?

13:40.277 --> 13:42.112
Damn it.

15:15.205 --> 15:17.249
I thought you threw up a lot.

15:17.833 --> 15:19.168
I need to fill up again

15:20.294 --> 15:21.295
since I threw up a lot.

15:29.887 --> 15:32.139
"If I can't prove myself by succeeding,

15:33.098 --> 15:35.100
I'll prove myself by falling apart."

15:36.185 --> 15:39.229
I feel proud
because I really fell apart today.

15:39.730 --> 15:43.025
It's the feeling of a day well spent.

15:47.655 --> 15:49.114
Doing it alone is exhausting.

15:50.699 --> 15:53.869
It's less exhausting when you have someone
telling you whether it's good or not.

15:56.372 --> 15:57.289
I'll stay by your side

15:57.915 --> 15:58.874
and watch you.

16:12.179 --> 16:13.764
Why do you keep covering it?

16:13.847 --> 16:14.682
Oh, well…

16:15.599 --> 16:16.433
This thing

16:17.309 --> 16:18.936
does that sometimes.

16:20.437 --> 16:21.522
I feel good.

16:22.523 --> 16:23.649
I'm sure I feel good.

16:24.817 --> 16:25.943
But the watch is red.

16:28.529 --> 16:30.280
When it was snowing earlier,

16:30.864 --> 16:33.784
the watch vibrated,
and I didn't even question it.

16:33.867 --> 16:36.203
I figured it'd be green.

16:37.162 --> 16:38.372
But it was red.

16:41.083 --> 16:42.001
I was curious

16:43.043 --> 16:43.961
and looked at it.

16:45.129 --> 16:46.171
It said, "lonely."

16:49.091 --> 16:51.719
So I thought,
"I guess I like being lonely."

16:52.803 --> 16:56.348
I guess it's no different from me

16:56.432 --> 16:58.517
liking things
like "destruction" and "hate."

16:59.601 --> 17:00.602
I'm the kind of guy

17:01.186 --> 17:03.063
who's anxious by default,

17:03.147 --> 17:05.232
so my watch turns red all the time.

17:05.315 --> 17:06.984
But when it does,

17:07.067 --> 17:09.820
I feel like I'm being rude
to the person in front of me.

17:10.446 --> 17:11.613
Don't you agree?

17:14.867 --> 17:16.535
If this ever hits the market,

17:17.119 --> 17:19.038
it'll destroy all relationships.

17:20.748 --> 17:22.332
Imagine couples wearing this.

17:23.751 --> 17:26.211
They claim to be in love and such,

17:26.837 --> 17:27.755
but it's not love.

17:30.924 --> 17:32.468
They say "love" doesn't appear.

17:34.094 --> 17:37.097
Because "love" is a concept,
not an emotion.

17:38.307 --> 17:39.641
Oh.

17:40.726 --> 17:41.727
I see.

17:42.394 --> 17:44.104
"Love" isn't an emotion.

17:44.188 --> 17:49.068
They say it just shows things like
"excited," "thrilled," or "nervous."

17:49.943 --> 17:52.321
What you're feeling in the moment.

17:53.238 --> 17:54.073
Right.

17:54.698 --> 17:56.200
How would you even detect love?

17:57.034 --> 17:58.744
Everyone's definition of love
is different.

18:00.037 --> 18:01.080
No wonder.

18:02.081 --> 18:05.209
The word "love"
always made me feel frustrated.

18:05.834 --> 18:07.920
Everyone keeps going on about love,

18:08.003 --> 18:10.255
so I wondered if I was the only one
who didn't know that feeling.

18:10.964 --> 18:14.468
I mean, I understand what it means
to long for or miss someone.

18:15.469 --> 18:17.721
But I kept wondering,
"What exactly is love?"

18:17.805 --> 18:19.848
"What is love?"

18:21.934 --> 18:22.851
What a huge relief.

18:26.605 --> 18:27.898
Now that I know it doesn't show "love,"

18:29.149 --> 18:31.026
I suddenly feel like I can trust it again.

18:33.278 --> 18:34.113
In that case,

18:35.239 --> 18:37.074
I can roll up my sleeve.

18:37.574 --> 18:39.493
Man, I was so worried

18:39.576 --> 18:41.370
that "love" would suddenly show up…

18:46.875 --> 18:48.502
I mean…

18:48.585 --> 18:49.419
What I mean is…

18:50.087 --> 18:51.922
Like a glitch, you know?

18:52.589 --> 18:54.842
I mean, I guess it's possible

18:55.425 --> 18:59.096
to love someone for a split second, right?

19:00.305 --> 19:02.182
Because we can't control how we feel.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.400
Anyway, there's no "love."

19:23.912 --> 19:24.746
By the way,

19:25.706 --> 19:26.748
can I text you?

19:27.666 --> 19:28.500
Of course.

19:30.627 --> 19:31.879
Can I text you anytime?

19:32.713 --> 19:33.589
Absolutely.

19:36.008 --> 19:37.467
I have no one to talk to now.

19:41.597 --> 19:43.473
-Can I really text you anytime?
-Yes, really.

19:44.016 --> 19:45.100
Okay.

20:09.249 --> 20:10.626
You'd better not beat me up again.

20:11.251 --> 20:12.794
How many times do I have to tell you?

20:12.878 --> 20:15.505
I'm not taking it
because your punches are stronger.

20:23.513 --> 20:25.224
You stuff your face like that
in public too?

20:37.694 --> 20:38.737
WE SELL GIMBAP

20:54.127 --> 20:57.464
EMPLOYMENT HISTORY RECORD
BYEON EUN-A, ADMIN ASSISTANT AT CHOI FILM

21:09.309 --> 21:10.852
What's he doing here?

21:13.855 --> 21:16.316
Why do I have a bad feeling about you
being here so early?

21:19.361 --> 21:20.570
The doors are opening.

21:27.995 --> 21:30.163
Your official statement
was nice and heartfelt.

21:31.873 --> 21:32.916
So what is it?

21:33.000 --> 21:34.793
-Did some other problem come up?
-The doors are closing.

21:44.261 --> 21:45.095
Get in.

21:50.809 --> 21:52.352
The doors are closing.

21:57.524 --> 21:58.900
Did you not go home last night?

22:00.402 --> 22:01.486
I did.

22:02.487 --> 22:03.864
Then why is your outfit the same?

22:05.699 --> 22:07.034
It's a different outfit.

22:23.342 --> 22:25.302
-Good morning, Mr. Choi.
-Hey.

22:25.969 --> 22:27.471
-Hello.
-Hello.

22:27.554 --> 22:28.889
Hello, yourself.

22:33.351 --> 22:35.687
Showing up this early means he's on edge.

22:35.771 --> 22:36.813
Who is he?

22:36.897 --> 22:38.356
The CEO of Oh Jeong-hui's agency.

22:43.028 --> 22:43.862
So?

22:44.529 --> 22:45.614
Did you find her daughter?

22:47.157 --> 22:47.991
Sorry?

22:50.160 --> 22:51.286
Where's your head at?

22:51.369 --> 22:53.413
I asked if you found
Oh Jeong-hui's daughter.

22:56.208 --> 22:57.042
Yes.

23:02.589 --> 23:03.715
Then what's with that look?

23:06.051 --> 23:07.052
What is it?

23:08.762 --> 23:11.056
Is her daughter absolutely furious?

23:14.684 --> 23:15.936
Damn, you're making me nervous!

23:16.019 --> 23:17.270
What is it?

23:18.897 --> 23:19.856
No.

23:20.440 --> 23:21.691
She's not furious.

23:22.984 --> 23:25.654
OH JEONG-HUI REFUTES CLAIMS
SHE NEGLECTED HER DAUGHTER

23:29.533 --> 23:31.827
"ALTHOUGH MS. OH WAS UNABLE TO BE
WITH HER DAUGHTER UNTIL THE END,

23:31.910 --> 23:34.246
SHE SOUGHT TO MAINTAIN THEIR RELATIONSHIP
EVEN AFTER THE DIVORCE."

23:37.874 --> 23:39.960
Just beg her to spare you.

23:40.043 --> 23:41.753
Get on your knees if you have to!

23:51.304 --> 23:52.722
The doors are closing.

24:32.429 --> 24:34.181
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

24:45.108 --> 24:47.152
Eun-a sent me her revision notes.

24:48.236 --> 24:49.321
And damn,

24:49.404 --> 24:50.989
she did an amazing job.

24:52.115 --> 24:52.991
It's pissing me off.

24:54.993 --> 24:56.995
There's a mountain of revisions to make,

24:58.371 --> 24:59.956
and she's right about all of it.

25:00.624 --> 25:02.083
Do you look blank now?

25:02.918 --> 25:04.294
This is so damn embarrassing.

25:04.878 --> 25:06.838
Stop crying and come out.
I'll treat you to barbecue.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.717
It has to be Jang Mi-ran, no matter what.

25:11.301 --> 25:13.970
I was up all night worrying
she'd turn it down right away.

25:14.596 --> 25:17.641
Then I texted her to read my screenplay,
and she called right away

25:18.391 --> 25:19.226
and suggested we meet.

25:20.060 --> 25:20.894
With you.

25:22.395 --> 25:23.521
Jang Mi-ran knows me?

25:24.814 --> 25:25.982
I doubt she even knows my name.

25:26.066 --> 25:29.152
She said she saw you
arguing with Gyeong-se in front of Agit.

25:33.531 --> 25:36.493
Goodness, has she fallen for me?

25:37.494 --> 25:38.703
Oh boy.

25:39.663 --> 25:42.249
She must hold a lot of resentment
toward Park Gyeong-se.

25:43.208 --> 25:46.044
If I had said everything
I prepared that day,

25:46.127 --> 25:47.379
it would've been game over.

25:48.964 --> 25:51.007
-Is she okay, by the way?
-What do you mean?

25:53.426 --> 25:55.095
About Oh Jeong-hui's real daughter.

25:55.929 --> 25:56.805
I mean,

25:57.472 --> 25:58.723
how's that Jang Mi-ran's problem?

25:59.557 --> 26:00.684
Don't bring it up later, okay?

26:00.767 --> 26:01.768
Why would I do that?

26:08.275 --> 26:09.234
Welcome.

26:09.943 --> 26:10.777
Wait.

26:12.362 --> 26:13.655
Jun-hwan.

26:13.738 --> 26:14.698
Hey.

26:15.323 --> 26:17.701
It's been a while. Good to see you.

26:18.201 --> 26:19.786
I heard you won the grant.

26:19.869 --> 26:20.787
Congratulations.

26:21.288 --> 26:22.956
Oh, it's nothing.

26:23.039 --> 26:24.416
All that hard work paid off.

26:25.875 --> 26:27.002
It's just the beginning.

26:31.172 --> 26:32.048
It's been a while, Dong-man.

26:34.509 --> 26:35.385
Yeah, it has.

26:36.678 --> 26:38.305
I was wondering how you were doing.

26:39.556 --> 26:40.432
I'm doing fine.

26:46.563 --> 26:47.564
What brings you here?

26:48.148 --> 26:50.025
Oh, I'm meeting Gi-yeong here.

26:50.108 --> 26:51.234
I see.

26:54.279 --> 26:55.655
-Excuse me.
-Sure.

26:57.699 --> 26:58.867
Hello?

26:59.743 --> 27:00.577
Yes, I see.

27:05.123 --> 27:05.999
Can we go somewhere else?

27:07.125 --> 27:08.585
But we're meeting her here.

27:15.091 --> 27:16.968
Seeing that jerk's face
pissed me right off.

27:18.887 --> 27:21.348
I've always thought
he was terrible at writing,

27:21.931 --> 27:24.225
even back when I was mentoring him
in film school.

27:24.726 --> 27:26.895
I've never seen anyone write
so badly and so cowardly.

27:29.314 --> 27:31.149
There's no substance in his writing.

27:32.067 --> 27:35.362
Instead, he obsesses over font styles
and line spacing like some pervert.

27:36.071 --> 27:37.947
He's an idiot who puts effort
into crap like that.

27:39.407 --> 27:41.618
I got pissed while reading his screenplay.

27:41.701 --> 27:45.538
He's the first bastard to make me think
I could commit murder.

27:45.622 --> 27:46.915
I feel attacked.

27:46.998 --> 27:49.417
I'm one of those idiots
who obsess over fonts now.

27:49.501 --> 27:51.169
Oh jeez. Have you lost your mind?

27:51.252 --> 27:53.963
When I like the font,
I feel like I like the writing more.

27:57.467 --> 27:58.551
Everyone is crazy.

27:59.052 --> 28:01.221
Investing three billion won
in a guy like him,

28:02.097 --> 28:04.057
and the production company
wanting to make it.

28:07.394 --> 28:09.145
Hye-jin's company is producing it.

28:11.815 --> 28:14.317
I'm just telling you so you won't slip up.

28:17.153 --> 28:18.238
It doesn't matter.

28:19.280 --> 28:21.116
I'm not in The Eight Club anymore.

28:33.962 --> 28:35.797
-Have you been well?
-Yeah.

28:36.965 --> 28:38.133
Do you have a producer lined up?

28:38.216 --> 28:39.342
No, not yet.

28:39.968 --> 28:41.886
No producer at Kopark Film
fits the schedule.

28:42.512 --> 28:45.807
Producers work back and forth
between Choi Film and Kopark Film.

28:46.391 --> 28:50.270
But the only good producer at Choi Film
is Producer Hyo-jin.

28:50.937 --> 28:51.938
What do you mean?

28:52.021 --> 28:53.356
There's Producer Byeon Eun-a.

28:53.857 --> 28:55.483
There are lots of capable people.

28:55.567 --> 28:56.943
Well, Producer Byeon Eun-a

28:57.694 --> 28:59.988
hasn't done much
to be considered a producer.

29:00.947 --> 29:03.324
What do you mean?
She's developed a handful of projects.

29:03.408 --> 29:06.119
Do you know how many she's saved
from being thrown out?

29:06.202 --> 29:07.203
That's what I don't like.

29:08.621 --> 29:12.083
It feels like whatever she picks is a dud.

29:13.334 --> 29:15.378
I hear she only goes for stuff
that's about to get tossed.

29:16.045 --> 29:17.547
You know, the ones below her level.

29:19.549 --> 29:21.551
Like some kind of underdog solidarity.

29:22.343 --> 29:23.595
No, that's not fair.

29:23.678 --> 29:26.347
Established directors
have their own producers in charge.

29:26.431 --> 29:30.143
Producer Byeon is just starting out,
so she works with a different pool.

29:32.228 --> 29:33.480
You shouldn't put it like that.

29:35.398 --> 29:36.900
Right, well…

29:37.817 --> 29:38.651
That's just how I see it.

29:42.864 --> 29:43.823
Dong-man,

29:45.325 --> 29:47.076
how come you're not making films?

29:51.080 --> 29:52.207
You think I'm choosing not to?

30:00.924 --> 30:01.966
Hi!

30:03.635 --> 30:05.178
Oh, you're here.

30:20.318 --> 30:21.486
Hello.

30:38.628 --> 30:40.630
What qualifies as a good poem?

30:45.635 --> 30:48.346
The ones experts recommend
are all so hard to understand.

30:55.478 --> 30:56.354
A poem…

30:59.065 --> 31:00.400
makes sense once you memorize it.

31:04.320 --> 31:05.822
You won't get it just by reading it.

31:21.212 --> 31:24.966
I've never met anyone who speaks so well
but is so bad at filming.

31:25.049 --> 31:27.051
Honestly, I didn't like the screenplay.

31:27.135 --> 31:28.136
I know, right?

31:28.219 --> 31:31.055
He said he'd explain it in person,
so I met him.

31:31.139 --> 31:32.765
I almost died laughing that day

31:32.849 --> 31:34.767
because he was so hilarious.

31:35.602 --> 31:37.687
I thought, "Was I wrong about it?"

31:38.479 --> 31:40.189
-I was fooled.
-You were fooled.

31:40.273 --> 31:41.691
Everyone does, all the time.

31:41.774 --> 31:43.776
You know the scene
where I had to saw my arm off?

31:43.860 --> 31:45.028
Guess how many takes it took.

31:47.989 --> 31:49.115
Cut!

31:49.198 --> 31:50.450
Let's try one more time.

31:50.533 --> 31:52.660
-The emotion's good, but…
-Scene 8, shot 7, take 17.

31:52.744 --> 31:54.203
Show me rage in the arm
that's still attached,

31:54.287 --> 31:56.080
and sadness in the other. Action!

31:57.165 --> 31:58.124
Cut!

31:58.207 --> 31:59.417
It looks like you're playing the violin.

32:00.627 --> 32:03.963
Cut! Can you add
about 10-won worth of sadness?

32:05.632 --> 32:06.549
Cut!

32:07.050 --> 32:08.051
Action!

32:11.429 --> 32:12.430
He said I lacked soul.

32:13.222 --> 32:15.224
Who has a soul
when they're sawing their own arm off?

32:15.308 --> 32:17.477
Who in their right mind
would saw their arm off?

32:17.977 --> 32:23.107
I kept sawing like I was actually
cutting off my own arm.

32:23.191 --> 32:26.110
I kept going until I was half-dead
and the sun came up.

32:30.239 --> 32:31.407
Cut.

32:33.076 --> 32:34.202
That's good for now.

32:34.285 --> 32:36.579
Let's call it a day here.
Good work, everyone.

32:37.121 --> 32:39.040
-Good job.
-Great work today.

32:40.208 --> 32:41.292
Can you get the right side?

32:51.052 --> 32:52.428
It felt like I was missing an arm.

32:54.097 --> 32:55.431
I couldn't feel it.

32:57.684 --> 32:59.435
I really sawed it off

33:00.186 --> 33:01.145
in my head.

33:02.730 --> 33:04.941
After that, I can't really use
my left arm anymore.

33:05.024 --> 33:06.234
I'm still like this.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.700
After all that method acting,

33:13.783 --> 33:17.996
Sister Vengeance was roasted online
as Tone-deaf Sister Vengeance.

33:18.621 --> 33:20.123
After that, whenever I see a weird scene,

33:20.206 --> 33:22.875
I get pissed because I know
it'll make me look like an idiot.

33:22.959 --> 33:25.545
And how many screenplays start off strong
but fall flat by the end?

33:25.628 --> 33:29.132
A smart, put-together woman
suddenly turns into a moron by the end.

33:29.799 --> 33:31.467
I'd stay up all night wondering

33:31.551 --> 33:34.137
how I could channel my inner moron
to play the role.

33:35.430 --> 33:37.765
Then I thought,
"Forget it. I'll write one myself."

33:38.391 --> 33:43.438
"I'll write one myself instead of living
at the mercy of garbage screenplays."

33:44.480 --> 33:45.440
Why don't you come to my class?

33:46.941 --> 33:48.526
No, I don't want to learn.

33:49.110 --> 33:51.070
Nothing's more boring than formal writing.

33:51.154 --> 33:54.073
I hate hearing about crap
like authenticity and story structure.

33:54.157 --> 33:56.617
You just have to write recklessly
and perform recklessly.

33:56.701 --> 33:58.077
-You're right.
-Right?

33:58.161 --> 33:59.829
-You have to be reckless.
-Exactly.

33:59.912 --> 34:00.788
Here's to being reckless.

34:00.872 --> 34:02.206
-Reckless!
-Reckless!

34:03.332 --> 34:05.251
Is one guy writing all the screenplays
in this country?

34:05.334 --> 34:06.919
How are they all the same?

34:07.003 --> 34:09.714
Then they ask the actor
if they can show another side.

34:09.797 --> 34:13.801
-Fetch me a different screenplay, then!
-Fetch it.

34:13.885 --> 34:15.970
-Fetch me a drink.
-Oh, okay.

34:18.431 --> 34:19.724
"Write your screenplays like that!"

34:19.807 --> 34:22.101
When you said that,

34:23.061 --> 34:25.563
my arm started twitching.

34:25.646 --> 34:28.066
Like a dead person
suddenly opening their eyes.

34:28.149 --> 34:29.650
It kept twitching.

34:31.277 --> 34:34.989
You know what
Park Gyeong-se's nickname used to be?

34:35.073 --> 34:36.324
What?

34:36.407 --> 34:37.575
"Watermelon Licker."

34:38.159 --> 34:40.369
He just needs to crack into it

34:40.453 --> 34:43.414
and at least give the audience a taste,

34:43.498 --> 34:44.540
but he can't.

34:44.624 --> 34:47.502
He just keeps carefully

34:48.044 --> 34:49.629
licking at it.

34:49.712 --> 34:53.216
Please stop licking it
and give us a taste already.

34:53.299 --> 34:54.258
That's what I'm saying.

34:54.342 --> 34:58.012
It's a sweet, juicy watermelon,
but he says,

34:58.096 --> 35:00.056
"I can't cut into this.
This is the best I can do."

35:00.139 --> 35:02.266
"Let's all give it a lick.
You'll feel the juice."

35:02.350 --> 35:03.309
What the hell?

35:03.893 --> 35:05.603
Oh? My goodness.

35:05.686 --> 35:06.687
It's moving again.

35:07.313 --> 35:09.107
It's twitching.

35:13.694 --> 35:15.363
Park Gyeong-se is a bastard
Damn Gyeong-se is a bastard

35:15.446 --> 35:17.156
He turns actors into morons

35:17.240 --> 35:19.826
What's my talent?

35:19.909 --> 35:21.244
Licking watermelons

35:21.828 --> 35:23.162
-Licking watermelons
-Licking watermelons

35:23.246 --> 35:24.872
Licking watermelons

35:24.956 --> 35:27.166
Licking… Oh!

35:30.586 --> 35:31.420
Holy crap.

36:03.452 --> 36:05.204
Are you trying to scare me with bad news?

36:05.830 --> 36:06.956
Why are you stalling?

36:10.251 --> 36:12.253
She changed her name

36:13.087 --> 36:15.673
from Byeon Si-on to Byeon Eun-a.

36:18.134 --> 36:19.802
-"Eun-a"?
-Yes.

36:22.805 --> 36:26.559
And she turned out to be closer
than I thought.

36:28.019 --> 36:29.270
She works at…

36:32.315 --> 36:33.858
Choi Film.

36:34.692 --> 36:37.361
I went there just in case,

36:38.529 --> 36:41.908
but no one seemed to know
that she's your daughter.

36:42.742 --> 36:46.287
If they knew, I don't think Mr. Choi
would have made such a fuss

36:46.370 --> 36:48.289
to find your daughter.

36:48.372 --> 36:50.666
And if he knew she was your daughter,

36:52.126 --> 36:53.377
would he treat her so badly?

36:55.880 --> 36:59.800
It's to the point where you almost wonder
if she's unaware of who her mother is.

36:59.884 --> 37:01.302
No one around her has any idea.

37:04.305 --> 37:08.100
She started as a contract admin assistant
and then went full-time.

37:08.726 --> 37:12.480
Considering that she worked similar jobs
after graduating high school,

37:13.773 --> 37:16.234
I don't think
she intentionally joined Choi Film.

37:18.903 --> 37:21.489
That man didn't even send her to college?

37:26.077 --> 37:28.579
Mr. Byeon Jae-su passed away in 2008,

37:29.664 --> 37:32.458
so she lives with her grandmother now.

37:35.586 --> 37:36.587
What grandmother?

37:37.588 --> 37:40.174
Both of her grandmothers have passed away.

37:40.758 --> 37:42.009
The thing is…

37:43.552 --> 37:46.055
Mr. Byeon Jae-su remarried--

37:46.138 --> 37:47.515
I know that.

37:47.598 --> 37:48.641
So…

37:49.433 --> 37:51.519
it's his second wife's…

37:52.979 --> 37:54.272
mother.

37:54.939 --> 37:57.942
She's living with her step-grandmother.

38:05.408 --> 38:07.159
Grandma, put it in here.

38:09.578 --> 38:11.539
They've been living together

38:12.164 --> 38:14.542
since Mr. Byeon remarried when she was 11.

38:15.835 --> 38:18.421
Even after he passed away
when she was in middle school,

38:19.046 --> 38:21.799
they continued to live together.

38:22.717 --> 38:25.303
It's not that good. Your gimbap is better.

38:31.225 --> 38:34.854
And her stepmother is in Japan for work.

38:57.335 --> 38:59.754
It's okay, just take a seat. I'll do it.

39:22.068 --> 39:26.322
We need to have her move before reporters
find out she's living in such a place

39:26.906 --> 39:29.492
and probably have her cut ties
with her grandmother too.

39:29.575 --> 39:32.745
I'll call her and tell her
to move out as soon as…

39:33.662 --> 39:34.789
Don't call her.

39:34.872 --> 39:36.332
I don't want anyone calling her.

39:36.415 --> 39:38.125
-I'll do it myself.
-Okay.

39:40.961 --> 39:41.962
Where's Mi-ran?

39:42.046 --> 39:44.090
She said she had plans
with Director Lee Jun-hwan tonight.

39:44.173 --> 39:45.800
She should be with him right now.

39:45.883 --> 39:47.802
Tell her not to drink
and to go home early.

39:48.427 --> 39:49.428
Understood.

40:12.493 --> 40:13.869
I'm on my way now.

40:13.953 --> 40:15.538
Yes, I'm in the car.

40:17.248 --> 40:18.624
She's the one who's in trouble.

40:18.707 --> 40:20.000
Take your time reading this.

40:21.502 --> 40:24.004
-Let's meet up again. Promise?
-Okay.

40:24.588 --> 40:26.090
Yes, of course. We promise.

40:26.173 --> 40:28.175
Get home safely.

40:28.259 --> 40:29.969
Have a good night.

40:30.052 --> 40:31.929
-Good night.
-Bye!

40:32.012 --> 40:33.097
-See you again!
-Okay.

40:46.485 --> 40:48.362
Let's share a taxi. I'll drop you off.

40:50.990 --> 40:52.032
Let's go together!

41:11.635 --> 41:14.638
The 46th Korean Film Awards
Best New Director Award goes to…

41:16.098 --> 41:18.726
Hwang Dong-man for Weather Maker!

42:02.645 --> 42:03.604
Hey, Ax.

42:05.439 --> 42:07.525
I hear you'll be working
with Hwang Dong-man.

42:08.984 --> 42:10.861
You're on my payroll,

42:12.238 --> 42:13.864
but you're taking work from outside?

42:15.241 --> 42:18.327
You know that many people
ask me to review their screenplays.

42:18.994 --> 42:20.663
That doesn't even count as work.

42:21.247 --> 42:22.248
Hwang Dong-man

42:23.123 --> 42:26.293
was under CEO Ko Hye-jin's wing
for ten years before she gave up.

42:27.002 --> 42:29.171
You think she gave up
because she's not as good as you?

42:29.255 --> 42:31.340
For the love of god, Ax.

42:31.423 --> 42:33.509
Stop digging through other people's trash.

42:34.426 --> 42:37.054
You only review screenplays
that are seconds from the shredder.

42:37.137 --> 42:40.432
I bet you only support the underdog team
when you watch sports.

42:41.600 --> 42:43.602
You think your workplace
is where you build your humanity?

42:44.478 --> 42:45.854
You think that's what I'm paying you for?

42:46.689 --> 42:49.858
If we only work with directors
who have already proven themselves,

42:50.609 --> 42:53.529
who will discover
the breakout rookie directors?

42:53.612 --> 42:55.656
You don't have to do that!

42:55.739 --> 42:59.994
People who have money
just focus on those who are a sure bet.

43:00.077 --> 43:02.955
Only people with no money
go around digging through trash.

43:03.664 --> 43:04.707
When you get to my age,

43:05.291 --> 43:07.251
you can just tell at a glance

43:08.210 --> 43:10.170
who's going to make it and who won't.

43:10.754 --> 43:13.757
There's no such thing
as a tragic genius or a hidden expert.

43:13.841 --> 43:16.927
Money just follows people
who are destined to make money.

43:17.011 --> 43:18.804
They can't hide from it
even if they wanted to.

43:18.887 --> 43:20.014
Do you see me hiding?

43:21.056 --> 43:23.934
So stop rummaging through trash!

43:28.022 --> 43:28.856
Throw them all out.

43:30.107 --> 43:32.026
How frustrating.

43:34.486 --> 43:37.990
Why would a successful director
work with small fries like us?

43:41.410 --> 43:43.203
I don't get it.

43:45.581 --> 43:48.542
I can't credit you as a writer.
I'll list you as a development producer.

43:48.626 --> 43:49.627
That's the best I can do.

43:58.427 --> 43:59.887
Are you kidding me?

44:04.016 --> 44:05.893
Stop leaving me on read,

44:05.976 --> 44:08.145
or else I'll show up at your place
and turn it upside down.

44:16.820 --> 44:18.697
I wish I had an older brother.

44:20.699 --> 44:22.368
A crazy-ass older brother.

44:34.046 --> 44:35.673
The wedding is right around the corner.

44:35.756 --> 44:39.635
I need a straight answer
on whether you've booked someone or not.

44:39.718 --> 44:41.387
I've called you dozens of times.

44:41.970 --> 44:42.930
What are you going to do?

44:43.555 --> 44:45.015
I bragged to the in-laws

44:45.099 --> 44:47.518
that a famous singer
would perform the wedding song.

44:47.601 --> 44:49.144
Am I supposed to tell them
it's not happening anymore?

44:49.228 --> 44:50.771
I'll lose face!

44:50.854 --> 44:54.233
You've been in that industry for 20 years,
and you have no one to ask?

44:57.778 --> 44:59.405
WEATHER MAKER

45:05.786 --> 45:07.913
MA JAE-YEONG, YOU PIECE OF SHIT

45:17.840 --> 45:20.467
MA JAE-YEONG'S "KNOCK, KNOCK, KNOCK"
AWARDED KFA'S GRANT

45:22.594 --> 45:24.596
…A PSYCHOLOGICAL FANTASY
THAT OPENS A THOUSAND DOORS…

45:27.391 --> 45:29.852
A THOUSAND DOORS

45:31.186 --> 45:32.896
Can you get me Ma Jae-yeong's screenplay?

45:34.273 --> 45:36.108
He'll show it to you if you ask.

45:36.775 --> 45:39.486
Or maybe you can ask Hye-jin.

45:40.821 --> 45:42.489
I just need to check something.

45:43.824 --> 45:45.159
That piece of shit.

45:45.242 --> 45:47.369
KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK

45:47.453 --> 45:48.579
For as long as I can remember,

45:49.580 --> 45:53.000
I've never seen people as just people.
I saw them as masses.

45:53.083 --> 45:54.460
Masses of emotion.

45:54.543 --> 45:57.004
PEOPLE ARE ALL… MASSES OF EMOTION

46:00.048 --> 46:01.091
You seem like someone

46:01.675 --> 46:04.470
who's got all thousand doors wide open.

46:04.553 --> 46:06.388
JI-WON: (MUTTERING) A THOUSAND DOORS…

46:21.278 --> 46:22.696
Don't you think we should meet?

46:23.530 --> 46:24.448
Why?

46:25.199 --> 46:26.492
Just tell me over the phone.

46:26.575 --> 46:28.660
If you don't come out,
I'm going to Ko Hye-jin.

46:29.703 --> 46:30.662
Want me to do that?

46:35.167 --> 46:37.044
Fucking hell.

46:37.920 --> 46:39.463
Fucking what?

46:41.048 --> 46:43.675
I should be the one swearing, you bastard.

46:44.676 --> 46:47.679
Have you ever seen someone
who's got all thousand doors wide open?

46:47.763 --> 46:49.723
Mine are all open.

46:49.806 --> 46:51.517
You're in real trouble, you punk.

46:52.434 --> 46:57.147
Forcing myself to read your writing
back in the day has finally paid off.

46:57.231 --> 46:59.650
So this is how I catch you, huh?

47:00.692 --> 47:01.985
I told you, didn't I?

47:02.069 --> 47:04.279
When you read someone's work,
you can see right through them.

47:04.863 --> 47:06.240
Like what they're thinking,

47:06.323 --> 47:09.326
what kind of person they are,
or how they've lived.

47:09.952 --> 47:12.162
So tell me this.

47:12.996 --> 47:14.748
Why am I seeing Byeon Eun-a
in your writing?

47:15.541 --> 47:16.625
Because we dated.

47:19.545 --> 47:21.213
I dated Byeon Eun-a.

47:22.047 --> 47:24.216
I know, you bastard!
I can see it in your writing!

47:24.800 --> 47:26.593
But why isn't she credited
on the screenplay?

47:27.177 --> 47:30.597
Do I have to credit every little help
I got from someone I was dating?

47:31.223 --> 47:33.809
Writing is like blood, so you can't
transfuse it unless it's the same type.

47:34.601 --> 47:35.811
It clots and tangles.

47:35.894 --> 47:39.147
Your screenplay clearly has two people
with different blood types in it.

47:39.648 --> 47:41.817
Sharp and precise Byeon Eun-a,

47:41.900 --> 47:44.152
and dull, old-fashioned Ma Jae-yeong.

47:44.236 --> 47:47.322
I could go through your screenplay
and precisely pick out who wrote what,

47:47.406 --> 47:49.199
without making a single mistake.

47:49.283 --> 47:50.284
Want me to do that?

47:51.493 --> 47:52.911
You think I'm the only one who can tell?

47:53.537 --> 47:55.956
I'll bet my life Ko Hye-jin knows too.

47:58.000 --> 48:00.252
You stole from someone you shouldn't have.

48:00.752 --> 48:02.588
You stole from a genius, you bastard.

48:02.671 --> 48:06.008
You stole from someone
who shines like a jewel.

48:06.091 --> 48:10.053
Someone so unmistakably bright
there's no way you wouldn't know it's her.

48:10.137 --> 48:11.638
But what did you say?

48:12.472 --> 48:13.724
You don't like her work?

48:15.642 --> 48:17.811
She only goes for duds
about to get tossed?

48:19.813 --> 48:21.023
You call that manners?

48:23.066 --> 48:24.901
Unlike you, that shining woman

48:25.652 --> 48:27.654
sets aside her own greed and desire

48:27.738 --> 48:29.781
and picks up the ones
that are about to get scrapped.

48:30.490 --> 48:32.784
Isn't it remarkable
that she uses her talent

48:32.868 --> 48:34.911
for what others would toss out?

48:35.746 --> 48:38.081
-You should put her on a pedestal!
-Goddamn it!

48:39.374 --> 48:41.084
Save your lecture
until you've proven yourself.

48:42.419 --> 48:45.297
You know what I realized
when you gave me so much crap?

48:46.214 --> 48:49.092
"I see. I remind this guy of himself."

48:49.843 --> 48:51.386
"He hates himself right now."

48:52.179 --> 48:55.057
You despised me
for being as incompetent as you

48:55.682 --> 48:57.142
and belittled me.

49:01.355 --> 49:02.522
You really think

49:03.940 --> 49:05.359
I'm still as incompetent as you?

49:12.407 --> 49:16.119
DIRECTOR HWANG DONG-MAN

49:40.227 --> 49:41.895
You said you'd text me.

49:59.496 --> 50:00.622
Thank you.

50:02.165 --> 50:03.500
Thanks to you,

50:04.251 --> 50:06.378
my watch turned green
for the first time today.

50:16.179 --> 50:17.097
Same here.

50:18.640 --> 50:20.517
Mine just turned green
for the first time today too.

51:18.283 --> 51:19.576
Jeez, who is it?

51:26.541 --> 51:28.084
My goodness.

51:29.795 --> 51:30.629
Hello?

51:32.756 --> 51:33.715
Are you sleeping?

51:34.633 --> 51:35.717
Yeah.

51:36.968 --> 51:38.094
Okay, go back to sleep.

51:38.804 --> 51:39.971
It's better that you sleep.

51:42.140 --> 51:43.850
Just listen as you sleep.

51:45.393 --> 51:46.311
Yeong-su.

51:46.978 --> 51:47.938
What?

51:48.688 --> 51:51.149
Why are you answering? Go back to sleep.

51:51.817 --> 51:52.901
Just go to sleep.

51:55.821 --> 51:57.239
I'll just talk to myself.

51:59.533 --> 52:01.660
This is embarrassing,
so I'll talk to myself.

52:01.743 --> 52:02.786
Go back to sleep.

52:05.163 --> 52:06.289
Yeong-su.

52:16.341 --> 52:18.468
Nobody knows about this.

52:20.428 --> 52:22.430
Not even Hye-jin.

52:24.808 --> 52:27.310
It's a secret I'm taking to my grave.

52:28.812 --> 52:31.189
THE LUSTFUL BOTTLE OPENER

52:31.273 --> 52:33.942
You know my debut film,
The Lustful Bottle Opener?

52:34.025 --> 52:34.901
That was actually…

52:39.239 --> 52:40.615
about Dong-man.

52:48.456 --> 52:50.834
When we lived together back in college,

52:51.793 --> 52:53.545
he came home totally wasted one day.

52:54.504 --> 52:57.841
He said he'd given a bottle opener
as a gift to a girl he liked,

52:59.342 --> 53:02.679
but he saw it on Cheol-ho's fridge
and totally lost it.

53:03.805 --> 53:06.641
He said he tore the door off the fridge.

53:07.601 --> 53:10.228
He was drunk and rambling on and on,

53:11.229 --> 53:12.898
and I wanted to write it all down.

53:15.734 --> 53:18.111
Because everything he said
as he was flipping out was hilarious.

53:22.407 --> 53:24.117
I lay down to go to sleep,

53:25.493 --> 53:28.330
but scenes started unfolding
before my eyes.

53:29.414 --> 53:30.624
A lackey in a gang

53:31.625 --> 53:34.377
gave a bottle opener as a gift
to a woman he liked…

53:34.461 --> 53:35.587
Monte Cristo.

53:38.048 --> 53:40.467
…but sees it on his boss's fridge.

53:41.760 --> 53:43.053
I knew it'd be a hit.

53:43.136 --> 53:44.387
I wrote it in three days.

53:45.263 --> 53:47.432
After that, I couldn't sleep
because it was too good.

53:49.059 --> 53:50.727
I kept thinking,
"This is Dong-man's story."

53:50.810 --> 53:53.021
"What if he says
he wants to write it himself?"

53:54.898 --> 53:56.149
But that idiot…

53:59.194 --> 54:00.445
didn't remember anything.

54:02.948 --> 54:05.700
He was so drunk that he blacked out.

54:06.868 --> 54:09.537
I've been on pins and needles ever since.

54:12.040 --> 54:13.875
Even during the premiere,

54:13.959 --> 54:16.670
I was afraid he'd suddenly remember
while watching it.

54:17.170 --> 54:18.296
Goddamn it.

54:18.922 --> 54:20.924
I hoped he'd just die in an accident.

54:23.593 --> 54:24.844
That's when I started

54:26.304 --> 54:27.889
to act snarky toward him.

54:33.103 --> 54:34.145
You already know…

54:36.564 --> 54:37.565
I'm sick of hearing

54:39.234 --> 54:42.529
that my debut film is my best work.

54:45.281 --> 54:46.908
Whenever I hear that…

54:51.037 --> 54:53.581
But if Dong-man suddenly gets his debut,

54:54.624 --> 54:56.543
and his film is actually good…

54:58.878 --> 54:59.796
Then…

55:04.467 --> 55:06.302
That'd make me nothing.

55:08.430 --> 55:09.305
That's why…

55:13.059 --> 55:15.687
I wished that the bastard
would never debut.

55:18.231 --> 55:20.191
I hoped he'd just disappear.

55:24.821 --> 55:26.031
Dong-man

55:26.740 --> 55:28.450
never showed it in front of you,

55:30.493 --> 55:32.454
but he really liked
The Lustful Bottle Opener.

55:33.872 --> 55:35.040
He liked it so much

55:35.707 --> 55:37.625
that he said he could almost kiss you.

55:39.919 --> 55:42.672
He said he wanted to make a film like it
before he died.

55:45.258 --> 55:46.509
That's how much he loved it.

56:03.151 --> 56:04.235
Were you awake?

56:09.449 --> 56:10.450
Why aren't you sleeping?

56:12.452 --> 56:13.953
Jeez, why aren't you sleeping?

56:16.206 --> 56:18.083
There's no need to be so on edge.

56:19.626 --> 56:22.962
We all use other people's stories
all the time.

56:24.672 --> 56:28.051
Even if you had told Dong-man,
he wouldn't have made it work.

56:28.968 --> 56:31.763
How many good stories has he let slip by?

56:34.265 --> 56:36.017
If he just wrote about his own stories,

56:36.726 --> 56:38.394
he'd have made three or four films by now.

56:40.271 --> 56:42.107
He doesn't realize
how good his stories are

56:43.066 --> 56:44.818
and keeps trying to force something out.

57:08.133 --> 57:09.050
Gyeong-se.

57:10.635 --> 57:12.262
It must've been really hard for you.

57:14.722 --> 57:15.974
That was a beautiful confession.

57:17.642 --> 57:19.060
You deserve a round of applause.

57:30.613 --> 57:32.949
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

57:33.032 --> 57:34.075
Is there anyone here

57:34.826 --> 57:36.661
who hasn't written about Dong-man?

57:38.204 --> 57:39.080
Ki-ri.

57:40.039 --> 57:43.543
The troublemaking brother-in-law
in X-Family is Dong-man, right?

57:45.003 --> 57:46.004
Seung-tae.

57:46.713 --> 57:48.423
In You Drive Me Crazy,

57:48.506 --> 57:50.592
the idiot loan shark is Dong-man, right?

57:51.676 --> 57:55.013
Whenever Dong-man talks,
everyone's eyes light up

57:55.096 --> 57:56.764
at the thought of using it later.

57:57.891 --> 57:59.392
You know this. I know this.

58:00.101 --> 58:01.102
We all do.

58:01.728 --> 58:02.896
Hey, Woo Seung-tae.

58:03.563 --> 58:06.649
You just openly take notes on your phone.

58:06.733 --> 58:08.318
That day when he went from ER to ER,

58:08.401 --> 58:10.862
threw up, and made a scene
trying to fish out a 500-won coin.

58:12.030 --> 58:14.449
You really think
no one will write about it?

58:16.367 --> 58:17.202
Hey, Gyeong-se.

58:18.119 --> 58:20.079
That story about
the National Stress Management Department.

58:20.163 --> 58:21.623
Can you finish that without Dong-man?

58:24.000 --> 58:25.251
I want you to think about

58:26.169 --> 58:30.173
how many ideas he's given us
while driving us up the wall.

58:31.257 --> 58:32.133
Just think.

58:33.384 --> 58:34.385
Now tell me…

58:36.471 --> 58:37.680
if we should still get rid of him.

58:40.183 --> 58:42.769
We're all relieved
because he's so clueless

58:42.852 --> 58:46.689
and doesn't even realize we're using him.

58:46.773 --> 58:47.982
But we still feel guilty,

58:48.983 --> 58:50.193
so we get snarky with him.

58:52.487 --> 58:53.363
Am I wrong?

58:54.697 --> 58:58.576
Do you think you can come up with ideas
without Dong-man?

59:01.287 --> 59:02.121
Okay, then.

59:03.373 --> 59:05.375
Do I get to have Hwang Dong-man to myself?

59:06.251 --> 59:07.085
Huh?

59:08.878 --> 59:09.754
Fine.

59:10.713 --> 59:12.465
Starting today, I'm his best friend.

59:13.049 --> 59:15.385
Everything that happens to him
is mine to write about.

59:15.468 --> 59:17.679
You can't use any of them
without my permission.

59:19.556 --> 59:20.640
Come on, Yeong-su.

59:22.141 --> 59:25.019
That's not how you end a scene.

59:26.187 --> 59:28.773
You know I'm not good at endings.

59:30.567 --> 59:33.152
I've already revised the ending 27 times.

59:35.321 --> 59:36.656
Whatever.

59:37.407 --> 59:38.241
In any case,

59:38.741 --> 59:39.909
Hwang Dong-man is mine.

59:40.535 --> 59:42.328
I'm old and don't have any ideas.

59:42.912 --> 59:43.913
Hwang Dong-man…

59:45.206 --> 59:46.332
Hwang Dong-man is mine.

59:51.754 --> 59:53.131
Why aren't you saying anything?

59:57.260 --> 59:58.303
Not you.

59:59.596 --> 01:00:02.015
I'm sure you have a lot to say.

01:00:06.853 --> 01:00:07.854
I'm against it.

01:00:09.397 --> 01:00:11.774
I'm against Director Hwang
rejoining The Eight Club.

01:00:15.069 --> 01:00:16.863
I don't want him seeing anyone but me.

01:00:17.572 --> 01:00:18.406
Why?

01:00:19.157 --> 01:00:20.199
You want him for yourself too?

01:00:20.992 --> 01:00:21.826
Yes.

01:00:22.619 --> 01:00:23.786
I want him all to myself

01:00:25.288 --> 01:00:28.499
and then give everything back to him.

01:00:29.208 --> 01:00:30.126
So he can see…

01:00:34.172 --> 01:00:37.342
how brilliant he really is.

01:00:56.444 --> 01:00:58.446
Why didn't you tell me you've got a girl?

01:00:59.864 --> 01:01:00.698
What?

01:01:01.282 --> 01:01:03.534
I told you I'd lift the ban
when you get a girlfriend.

01:01:06.454 --> 01:01:08.456
It's a one-way crush.

01:01:08.539 --> 01:01:10.875
Hey, don't spread any rumors.

01:01:10.958 --> 01:01:12.293
If Eun-a finds out…

01:01:13.419 --> 01:01:15.213
Don't, okay? I'm serious.

01:01:15.296 --> 01:01:16.714
It's not one-sided.

01:01:16.798 --> 01:01:18.424
She's openly taking your side.

01:01:20.968 --> 01:01:22.220
You're no longer banned.

01:01:27.183 --> 01:01:29.477
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

01:01:29.560 --> 01:01:31.104
Goodness me.

01:02:05.972 --> 01:02:08.307
That idiot better not go up there
and sing himself.

01:02:08.391 --> 01:02:09.976
I'll drag him off the stage.

01:02:11.561 --> 01:02:14.105
Please welcome the guest singer
with a big round of applause.

01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:15.523
Now,

01:02:16.315 --> 01:02:17.150
the wedding song.

01:02:30.037 --> 01:02:31.664
I'd like to congratulate

01:02:31.748 --> 01:02:34.625
Director Hwang Dong-man's cousin,
Ms. Lee Ye-rin,

01:02:34.709 --> 01:02:37.795
and her groom, Mr. Kim Sin-yeong,
on their wedding.

01:02:37.879 --> 01:02:40.006
I'd also like to thank
Director Hwang Dong-man

01:02:40.089 --> 01:02:44.552
for healing my arm that got injured
while filming Sister Vengeance.

01:02:44.635 --> 01:02:45.553
Director Hwang,

01:02:45.636 --> 01:02:49.432
don't forget I'm first in line
for your next amazing screenplay.

01:02:50.266 --> 01:02:52.226
Now for the wedding song.

01:02:55.146 --> 01:02:58.858
Excuse me, just a moment
We're still strangers for now

01:02:58.941 --> 01:03:02.779
But soon enough
We'll be an addictive game

01:03:02.862 --> 01:03:07.116
This feeling I'm feeling right now
Like it's connecting us

01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:10.328
Like ice cream that's melting away

01:03:10.411 --> 01:03:13.164
Right now, this feels like a dream

01:03:13.247 --> 01:03:17.084
You and me, dancing together

01:03:17.168 --> 01:03:20.755
The feeling is so incredible
It's like art

01:03:20.838 --> 01:03:24.634
Ooh-eh-oh, ooh-eh-oh, ooh-eh-oh

01:03:30.056 --> 01:03:32.683
I'm not even hoping for success.

01:03:34.977 --> 01:03:36.813
I just want to make one film.

01:03:38.648 --> 01:03:42.443
So I can overcome this feeling
of worthlessness, even just a little.

01:04:22.483 --> 01:04:24.277
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

01:04:42.378 --> 01:04:44.463
I should've fallen in love.

01:04:44.547 --> 01:04:47.466
Who knew I had
such a powerful engine inside me?

01:04:47.550 --> 01:04:49.135
I should've fallen in love.

01:04:49.218 --> 01:04:52.471
Byeon Eun-a can revive dead scripts,
and now she's backing Hwang Dong-man.

01:04:52.555 --> 01:04:54.056
Think this through.

01:04:54.140 --> 01:04:55.600
Another person came forward.

01:04:55.683 --> 01:04:57.393
There's even a photo
from when she was young.

01:04:57.476 --> 01:05:00.730
Excuse me.
Please answer Ms. Oh Jeong-hui's call.

01:05:00.813 --> 01:05:02.690
Forget it. I'll tell them myself.

01:05:02.773 --> 01:05:04.775
On live TV, in front of the whole country.

01:05:04.859 --> 01:05:07.236
They showed the same pattern as you again.

01:05:07.320 --> 01:05:09.572
I've never gotten an "unknown."

01:05:09.655 --> 01:05:10.698
Why does…

01:05:11.282 --> 01:05:12.992
Why does that person feel that way?

01:05:13.075 --> 01:05:17.830
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
